                <!-- Slide 0: Module Introduction -->
                <div class="slide active" data-slide-num="0">
                    <h2>Module Introduction</h2>
                    
                    <p>Welcome to the <strong>Investigations</strong> module, part of <strong>CLEAR's Regulation 101 Microlearning Series</strong> within our <strong>How We Regulate</strong> track.</p>

                    <p>When something goes wrong, such as allegations of sexual misconduct, embezzlement, falsification of records, regulatory agencies must respond. Unlike inspections, which proactively ensure compliance, <strong>investigations are reactive actions taken after an event has occurred</strong>.</p>

                    <p>An investigation is an in-depth inquiry and analysis into a complaint or allegation. It's detective work that requires planning, legal knowledge, evidence gathering, and careful documentation. The goal? To determine what happened, who was involved, and whether regulatory violations occurred.</p>

                    <p>Watch the video below to get started.</p>

                    <div class="video-container">
                        <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1143681371?h=61382ee3a0&badge=0&autopause=0&player_id=0&app_id=58479" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; encrypted-media" title="Licensure Introduction"></iframe>
                    </div>

                    <h3>Module Structure</h3>
                    
                    <p style="text-align: center; margin: 30px 0;">
                        <em>[Module structure image would display here]</em>
                    </p>

                    <h3>Learning Objectives</h3>
                    
                    <div class="objectives-list">
                        <p>Upon completing this module, you will be able to:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Define</strong> licensure and registration, and explain the difference between them</li>
                            <li><strong>List</strong> the key benefits that licensure provides to the public</li>
                            <li><strong>Identify</strong> the key components of a licensure process</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="highlight-box">
