                    <h2>Summary & Key Takeaways</h2>
                    
                    <h3>Learning Objectives Review</h3>
                    <div class="objectives-list">
                        <p><strong>You should now be able to:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Prepare</strong> an investigation plan using the six fundamental questions and understanding legal boundaries</li>
                            <li><strong>Identify</strong> the seven sources of investigative information</li>
                            <li><strong>Execute</strong> an investigation plan while remaining flexible to changing circumstances and documenting thoroughly</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <h3>Key Messages to Remember</h3>

                    <div class="concept-card burgundy">
                        <h4>Lesson 1 - Planning Your Investigation:</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Six fundamental questions: <strong>Who, What, When, Where, Why, How</strong></li>
                            <li>Planning for tools, equipment, budget, and travel</li>
                            <li>Understanding legal boundaries in your jurisdiction</li>
                            <li>When proper authorization (warrants, orders) may be required</li>
                            <li>Your investigation plan is both a roadmap and the foundation for your report</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="concept-card gold">
                        <h4>Lesson 2 - Seven Sources of Information:</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>üì¢ <strong>The Complainant</strong> - Foundation of investigation</li>
                            <li>üîç <strong>The Investigator</strong> - Institutional knowledge and previous cases</li>
                            <li>üëî <strong>The Respondent</strong> - Their version of events</li>
                            <li>üë• <strong>Witnesses</strong> - Third-party accounts</li>
                            <li>üìÅ <strong>Public Records</strong> - Objective, verified information</li>
                            <li>üîí <strong>Private Records</strong> - May require compulsory process</li>
                            <li>üî¨ <strong>Physical & Electronic Evidence</strong> - Tangible proof</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="concept-card blue">
                        <h4>Lesson 3 - Executing the Plan:</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Follow your roadmap while remaining flexible</li>
                            <li>Use Management by Objectives (MBO) to stay result-focused</li>
                            <li>Adapt methods while maintaining focus on objectives</li>
                            <li>Document everything‚Äîyour investigation must withstand scrutiny</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

